{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"918b1371-4fb1-4e57-bb12-17e6c6f00fb3","content":"In .NET MAUI, use the **lifecycle mapping events** configured in `MauiProgram.cs` via `ConfigureLifecycleEvents`:\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;\n\nbuilder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n{\n#if ANDROID\n    events.AddAndroid(android => android\n        .OnPause(activity => { /* your code */ })\n        .OnStop(activity => { /* your code */ }));\n#elif IOS\n    events.AddiOS(ios => ios\n        .DidEnterBackground(app => { /* your code */ }));\n#endif\n});\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- Add `using Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;`\n- Use `#if ANDROID` / `#elif IOS` preprocessor directives to keep platform code separated.\n- Each handler receives the native object (`Activity` on Android, `UIApplication` on iOS).\n- Other available Android events: `OnCreate`, `OnResume`, `OnDestroy`, etc.\n- Other iOS events: `WillEnterForeground`, `WillTerminate`, `OnActivated`, etc.\n\nThis avoids subclassing native platform classes and keeps all lifecycle logic in one place.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"065edc5d-ca49-4f9c-8c26-701e1665e5c9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to hook into platform-specific lifecycle events in .NET MAUI - specifically Android's OnPause/OnStop and iOS's DidEnterBackground. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without needing to search the codebase.","outputTokens":375,"requestId":"980F:204067:16351D0:18C5538:6A051EA1"},"id":"3dc9cbc9-f79c-4adf-bafd-2898b6c0aa06","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:00:25.206Z","parentId":"0b814739-8049-4b24-a0b7-d30e4ede763d"}
